Today we will check a few more 6th moves and then try another 5th move.
The 7th and 8th move are quite logical.
and white, knowing that passive style is hopeless,
Now, how should black continue, we should look carefully, to avoid traps.,
what is the idea of f5?
hard to explain in few words.
there is onthing we can do except f5,f8, f5 is better than f8?
Well, there may be some other plans besides f5.
However, f5 is the three, made of the only pai that was out of white control.
So it is logical that black uses the temporary tempo,
to create an additional stone, and a potential four for further game,
because likely black and white will be struggling for control,
so the potential black four would help black a lot.
especially, to avoid forbidden traps etc
White is forced to defend actively
However, in closer look we realize that white has no VCT>
in the end all is under white's control.
i am too deeply thinking of the diagram
white has the tempo but in black's control?
White used its only free pair
the pair 2_6 was under black's control.
and it is the last one
therefore, black plays g7, to grab the important point
SO, naturally active f6 may sometimes be more headache
so it is a win move.
Black defends firts, then attacks freely.,
white I8. try to make overline?
so maybe defend without giving black the k6 stone
ok, then we try use the four as lu said
It looks like black still wins after all the struggle
This is the win by theory.
13-g6 seems ok too as we just analysed together.
see how 10th move comes into play
so I just tell you to be careful
And the next move is hard to find
This happens if we do not plan black's attack carefully.

and in order to keep control, black must go on overline
Now, black has the whole right side for attacking space.
I have seen people using j9, or j10,
all related to right side power.
but sometimes it helps in line i6_k8
how come so many people think same way

Coz they all learn from you

we must make sure later if white could do any better moves there.
Move 23 connects left and right side
indeed, :) stone at right would be a waste
the upper side support is dead now
